tasks.description:
New i18n namespace with all user-visible strings for the conversations feature. No code dependencies — can proceed in parallel with service/API work.

Files to create:
- packages/i18n/src/locales/es/conversations.json — all keys for: form.*, status.*, inbox.*, thread.*, errors.*, email.*, empty.*, actions.*, notifications.*
- packages/i18n/src/locales/en/conversations.json — same structure, English copy
- packages/i18n/src/locales/pt/conversations.json — same structure, Portuguese copy

Key sections required (all values must be non-empty strings, no hardcoded copy in components):
  form: { name, namePlaceholder, email, emailPlaceholder, phone, phonePlaceholder, message, messagePlaceholder, charCount, submit, viewExisting }
  status: { open, pendingOwner, pendingGuest, closed, blocked, pendingVerification }
  inbox: { title, guestInboxTitle, ownerInboxTitle, lastMessage, unreadCount, accommodation, lastActivity, noSubject }
  thread: { title, readByOwner, readByGuest, systemMessage, replyPlaceholder, send, older, newest }
  errors: { rateLimitExceeded, conversationBlocked, tokenExpired, tokenRevoked, verificationExpired, verificationInvalid, messageContentBlocked, messageTooLong, conversationDuplicate, conversationNotFound, accommodationDeleted }
  email: { verify: { subject }, newMessage: { subject }, newMessageAnon: { subject }, tokenExpiringDay15: { subject }, tokenExpiringDay25: { subject } }
  empty: { guestInbox, ownerInbox }
  actions: { reply, close, reopen, block, archive, unarchive, requestAccess, viewConversation, deleteConversation }
  notifications: { verificationSent, messageSent, conversationClosed, conversationBlocked, conversationArchived }

Files to modify (if applicable):
- packages/i18n/src/index.ts or namespace registry — register 'conversations' namespace if it requires explicit registration

Acceptance criteria (refs: all UI-facing ACs, especially AC-001-01, AC-002-03, AC-003-01, AC-004-02):
- All three locale files parse as valid JSON
- pnpm typecheck passes
- All keys from the defined sections are present in all three locales
- No hardcoded English strings remain in any conversations component (verified at component implementation time)

Testing: JSON validity verified by the i18n package's own type-checking at build time. Component usage verified during T-014 and T-015.
